---
layout: home.njk
title: Timbers
description: A Git-native development ledger that records what changed, why it changed, and how the work was done.
permalink: /index.html
---
<section class="hero shell">
  <div class="hero-copy">
    <p class="eyebrow">Git-native development ledger</p>
    <h1>Timbers</h1>
    <p class="hero-statement">Git knows what changed.<br><strong>Timbers captures why.</strong></p>
    <p class="lede">Record the reasoning behind a change while it still exists, then turn that ledger into reports, release notes, and durable project context.</p>
    <div class="actions">
      <a class="button primary" href="https://github.com/gorewood/timbers/blob/main/docs/tutorial.md">Get started</a>
      <a class="button secondary" href="{{ ('/' + timbermill.collections[0].route + '/') | siteUrl }}">Read real outputs</a>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="command-line" aria-label="Install Timbers">
    <span aria-hidden="true">$</span>
    <code>curl -fsSL \
  https://raw.githubusercontent.com/gorewood/timbers/main/install.sh | bash</code>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="ledger-proof section-band">
  <div class="shell proof-grid">
    <div>
      <h2>Capture the synthesis, not the session.</h2>
      <p>Agent transcripts are exhaustive and temporary. A Timbers entry keeps the compact explanation that future maintainers actually need.</p>
    </div>
    <pre class="entry-sample" aria-label="Example Timbers ledger entry"><code><span>what</span>  Switched to cursor pagination

<span>why</span>   Offset pages duplicate items when
      writes happen between requests.

<span>how</span>   Opaque cursors encode created_at
      and id for a stable ordering.

<span>notes</span> Offset was simpler, but stability
      matters more for active feeds.</code></pre>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="workflow shell">
  <header class="section-heading">
    <h2>A ledger that stays close to the work</h2>
  </header>
  <ol class="workflow-steps">
    <li><h3>Commit the change</h3><p>Keep using Git as the source of implementation truth.</p></li>
    <li><h3>Record the reasoning</h3><p>Your agent snapshots what, why, how, and optional deliberation notes.</p></li>
    <li><h3>Publish useful context</h3><p>Query the ledger or render audience-specific reports when they are needed.</p></li>
  </ol>
</section>

<section class="outputs section-band">
  <div class="shell">
    <header class="section-heading">
      <h2>Project history people can use</h2>
    </header>
    {% for configured in timbermill.collections %}
      {% set configuredItems = collections['collection-' + configured.id] | byNewest %}
      <section class="collection-group" aria-labelledby="collection-{{ configured.id }}">
        <header class="group-heading">
          <h3 id="collection-{{ configured.id }}">{{ configured.label }}</h3>
          <a class="text-link" href="{{ ('/' + configured.route + '/') | siteUrl }}">Browse all</a>
        </header>
        <div class="output-list">
          {% for item in configuredItems | take(3) %}
            <article>
              <p class="artifact-meta">{% if configured.kind == 'native' %}Native artifact{% else %}Generated report{% endif %}{% if item.data.date %} · {{ item.data.date | displayDate }}{% endif %}</p>
              <h3><a href="{{ item.url | siteUrl }}">{{ item.data.title or item.fileSlug }}</a></h3>
              {% if item.data.summary %}<p>{{ item.data.summary }}</p>{% endif %}
            </article>
          {% endfor %}
        </div>
      </section>
    {% endfor %}
  </div>
</section>

<section class="closing shell reading-shell">
  <h2>Start with the next meaningful change.</h2>
  <p>Timbers stores plain structured entries alongside the code. No transcript archive and no hosted service are required.</p>
  <a class="button primary" href="https://github.com/gorewood/timbers/blob/main/docs/tutorial.md">Read the tutorial</a>
</section>
